    "course_title": "RESEARCH AND EVALUATION FOR EQUITY",
    "description": "Interdisciplinary approach to research and evaluation develops a critical approach to analyzing the quality and utility of monitoring and evaluation systems. Introduces common types of program evaluation. Focuses on the project, program, institutional, and systems levels to explore how monitoring and evaluation systems function in different settings. Asks how politics shape who evaluates, for what reasons, and with what consequences. Provides an overview of traditional and alternatives approaches to monitoring and evaluation",
